{{Top|leg}}
'''Tradechips''', sometimes spelled '''TradeChips''', were small computer chips designed to be collected and traded by children. They often contained small [[Hologram/Legends|holograms]] of a sports star or other celebrity, together with biographical information and other statistics.<ref name="HNN50" />

[[Spotts TradeChip Company]] manufactured tradechips during the final years of the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]], including the controversial [[Jedi TradeChips]] set in [[22 BBY/Legends|22 BBY]],<ref name="HNN50">{{HoloNetNewsWeb|50|jediwatch/1344_2.html|Jedi TradeChips Spark Controversy}}</ref> along with a series of [[Smashball]] tradechips.<ref name="Sports Part 2">{{SW|url=news/take-me-out-to-the-ballgame-sports-in-the-star-wars-galaxy-part-2|series=Sports in the Star Wars Galaxy|text=Part 2: Take Me Out to the Ball Game|nolive=1}}</ref>

